HEADWORD: Syringa
<hw>Sy*rin"ga</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr. Gr. <?/,
<?/, a shepherd's pipe, tube. Cf. <er>Syringe</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>A genus of plants; the lilac.</def>
<sd>(b)</sd> <def>The mock orange; -- popularly so called because its
